President Trump addressed the American Legion's national convention, thanking veterans for their service and promising to prioritize their care. He highlighted the progress made in reforming the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA), including publishing wait times online, delivering same-day emergency mental health services, and increasing the number of veterans approved to see the doctor of their choice. The president also signed the Veterans Appeals Improvement and Modernization Act, which aims to expedite the appeals process for veterans. He emphasized the need to build up the military and announced a new strategy in Afghanistan and South Asia. Trump also spoke about the importance of unity and working together to achieve a better future for the country. He closed by recognizing the heroism of Medal of Honor recipient Donald E. Ballard and thanking him for his service.